<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The use of mhd_assert(0) in the default/case tail may introduce an invariant controlling expression if the macro expands to a conditional (for example: if (!(0)) ... or if (0) ...). In that expansion the controlling expression is a constant (invariant) and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3. If, however, mhd_assert is defined to be a no-op (elided) in the translation unit, there is no invariant controlling expression in the source shown.
</scenario>
